#Fragment Britannia, Local, Britannia_Yew {
  #Sophistication High {
    #Key "*prison*" "*gaol*" "*jail*" {
      "Indeed we have the second largest prison in the realm. Those found guilty by the High Court are destined to be imprisoned just northwest of Yew for a while.",
      "The prison is past the High Court to the northwest ... although it is not a common tourist site. Usually people come here for the wine.",
      "The prison is not so much a part of Yew, as associated with the High Court. It is across the water from the city, to the northwest."
}
    #Key "*storehouse*" {
      "There is a prison storehouse between the High Court and the prison.",
      "The storehouse is mainly for the prison, of course. There's never been a need for the city to use those reserves, not that I know of.",
      "Yes, the prison storehouse is betwixt the court and the prison. They are all interconnected, of course."
}
    #Key "*court*" {
      "Most of the important decisions of the realm are reached in the High Court. Lord British himself comes when the rulings are of national interest! If thou wishes to see it, 'tis to the west and north of town.",
      "It was decided a long time ago that local judges would sit on the High Court. If thou wishes to see the court, head west and north of town. I cannot say if there is a trial in progress, however.",
      "Judges are elected yearly by the entire Britannian population, but we in Yew get an extra vote, since they also rule on local cases. It is nearby to Yew, and just across the strait from the prison."
}
    #Key "*flour*" "*mill*" {
      "If thou hast grain to be milled, take it to the flour mill just a bit west of the Abbey.",
      "Our flour mill is to the north side of town, across a bit of an inlet from the Abbey.",
      "We are lucky to have such a fine mill in town. It is only a bit of a walk north from the market area."
}
    #Key "*empath*" "*abbey*" {
      "The monks in the abbey that lies to the northeast spend their time studying painting, sculpting, prose, poetry, music ... and wine.",
      "Thou canst find an abbey to the northeast of Yew. There live the gentle monks who make the finest wines in the realm.",
      "Thou art interested in Empath Abbey, now? 'Tis a fine place of meditation and study. 'Tis on the northern edge of Yew, northeast of the craftsmen and past the winery."
}
    #Key "*wine*" {
      "Indeed, Yew is home to the finest vintner monks in the realm. They spend their days studying the art of wine, and their product only gets better. The winery is but a short walk south of the abbey.",
      "If thou art looking for the winery, head north of the craftsmen's shops. 'Tis very near the abbey, and just south of the vineyards.",
      "The vineyards and winery are just south of the abbey, to the east of the flour mill and across the little inlet."
}
    #Key "*healer*" {
      "The healers in Yew are specialized in natural cures. There are at least two in town: one is southeast and one is central.",
      "The potions our healers sell are part herbalistic and part alchemical. There is a shop in the center of Yew, close by the butcher and baker.",
      "Our healers try to gently persuade the elements into healing wounds, they never force nature to their needs. There is a healer's shop near by the cemetery, but take no ill omen of that."
}
    #Key "*market*" "*produce*" "*farm*" "*food*" {
      "Yew is more known for its sheep than for its farmland. A farmer imports fresh produce from outlying lands, and sells them at the market shop right next to the butcher.",
      "Fresh vegetables and other nourishing foods are sold at the market in the center of town. Look for a shop close by the butcher and baker.",
      "If thou'rt looking for farm-fresh food, thou needs to make a visit to the market in town."
}
    #Key "*butcher*" "*meat*"{
      "Fresh meat can be had from the butcher, in the clearing at the center of Yew.",
      "The butcher's shop is close by the baker and the farmer's market.",
      "Yew is a humble town, with no real pretensions to grandeur. There is but one central clearing, and that's where thou'lt find the butcher's shop."
}
    #Key "*baker*" {
      "We do have a baker, and a fine one at that. To find the bakery, find the market near the center of Yew. The baker hangs his sign between that of the butcher and the woodworker.",
      "Warm bread and other simple delights can be bought from the bakery at the center of Yew.",
      "Our baker is at the center of Yew, which lies between the winery and the northwestern inlet.",
      "The baker is somewhat between the bowyer and the woodworker."
}
    #Key "*wood*er*" {
      "Our woodworker is deft at staves and such things ... 'tis an old tradition going back to the earliest shepherds. There is a fine selection at the shop beside the bakery.",
      "Our woodworker's shop is in the clearing central to Yew. If thou couldst use a stout staff or some such thing, take the time to look at the goods there.",
      "Yew is famous for its wood crafts. There is a woodwork shop near the bakery, just a bit south of the bowyer."
}
    #Key "*cemetery*" {
      "The cemetery is to the south and east of town.",
      "It is a sad truth that there is no place safe ... even our serene woods can at any time be overrun with ettins and orcs. Those we have lost in such attacks are put to rest in the cemetery to the south.",
      "It is the way of nature for all things to pass from this world. The mortal remains of our loved ones lie in the cemetery to the southeast."
}
    #Key "*bowyer*" {
      "Fine yew bows are a specialty of Yew, naturally. We have an expert bowyer whose skill cannot be matched by any in the realm. Look north of the woodworker for the shop.",
      "If thou'rt handy with a bow and arrows, then surely thou'lt be interested in our bowyer's excellent work. Look in his shop at the center of town ... there a selection that'll make thy head spin.",
      "Indeed we have a bowyer! His shop is at the center of Yew, in that wee bit of a clearing with about five or six stores. Take a look around and see if thou likest anything."
}
    #Key "*britain*" "*capital*" {
      "Britain thou'rt askin' about? I'm told 'tis the biggest city in the land. Don't see what all t'fuss is about. The size of hereabouts is plenty big for me.",
      "Britain? I went there once. 'Tis over by the eastern shore, at the mouth of a whoppin' great river. That's where Lord British holds 'is court, but I saw him not even once.",
      "Britain? 'Tis the capital of the whole wide world, o'course. Sits on the shore of Britanny Bay way off yonder.",
      "Britain isn't so much as some folks thinks it is. They got lots of everything, but 'tis all flash and bother. Shiny nonsense....",
      "A place of magic, is Britain. Some say they invent a new spell every day. Don't know how they could use that many ....",
      "They're fair folk in Britain, mainly. A bit overloud for my tastes.",
      "Someday I'll go to Britain again, maybe settle down. They've got everything there ... games and shoppes and magic and just everything.",
      "Britain was the first place where people are judged according to their own accomplishments, not their fathers'. 'Tis a tricky thing to make work, I'd imagine.",
      "'Tis  the very center upon which all ill-natured rogues converge. They seek to destroy what they cannot understand.",
      "Britain? Seems a nice place, from what all I've heard.",
      "Britain? Been once. Quite big.",
      "Oh, posh. Britain's a place for swelled heads. All art and music and dilly dancin'. Bet there's not a soul there who likes rutabagas for breakfast.",
      "I hear the houses in Britain are too fine for bugs in the butter."
    }
    #KEY "*trinsic*" {
      "Trinsic? 'Tis near the Cape of Heroes, I think.",
      "If thou'rt looking for Trinsic, 'tis south, but along the eastern coast.",
      "Thou must be a fisher or an inventor if thou'rt interested in Trinsic. Fish, fighters and fools, that's what they've got.",
      "Trinsic is a clever place. They've got fellows there who spend all day thinkin' about weapons of war and other such things to improve the quality of life.",
      "I saw a combat mage on his way to Trinsic once. Said he was going to teach battle magic to the paladins.",
      "I met a man from Jhelom who said that Trinsic buys war horses like a shepherd buys apples!",
      "It's too smart for me there by half, and that's the truth. Trinsic is all engineers from Britain and Minoc and Moonglow. I'd be feared to speak for soundin' stupid.",
      "I don't know much about Trinsic. I think they make paladins or palaquins or something.",
      "Trinsic is a tough place. The whole thing is warriors, and the rest is city guards.",
      "There be giants, ogres and trolls near Trinsic ... and pirates in the waters.",
      "Trinsic? 'Tis the land's guardian, a city that teaches paladins the ways of honor and virtue.",
      "'Tis a place of swift justice, is Trinsic. Thieves are as rare as whistling cats."
    }
#Key "*okllo*" "*ocllo*" {
      "Ocllo? Doubt I heard of it.",
      "Ocllo? Island folks, I think.",
      "I've no ken of Ocllo.",
      "Ocllo ... hmmm. 'Tis an island, I believe.",
      "Ocllo ... rings a bell. Mayhaps something to do with salt ....",
      "Ocllo? Sounds very like the beginning of a joke!"
    }
#KEY "*jhelom*" {
